# Shayn MIS Backend — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Controller → Service → Repository. Never skip layers.
- Controllers: only HTTP. No db imports, no business logic.
- Services: orchestration and business rules. No res/req.
- Repositories: Sequelize only. Reads = sequelize.query(), Writes = Model methods.

## TypeScript
- strict: true. Zero `any`. Explicit return types on all exports.
- import type for type-only imports.
- Use path aliases: @db/*, @modules/*, @utils/*, @config/*, @constant, @middleware, @logger/*

## Patterns
- All env vars via environment object from @config/config (Zod-validated)
- All logging via logger from @logger/logger (Winston). Never console.log.
- Errors via AppError + handleErrorResponse. Never throw raw Error in controllers.
- Responses via handleApiResponse(res, { data }). Never res.json() directly.

## Database
- Reads: sequelize.query<T>(sql, { type: QueryTypes.SELECT, replacements: { :named } })
- Writes: Model.upsert(), Model.update(), Model.create(), Model.findOrCreate()
- Named params only: :paramName — never $1/$2 pg-style

## Modules
Each connector module has: connector.ts + sync.ts + backfill.ts
Each API module has: controller.ts + service.ts + repository.ts + routes.ts + types.ts
